<title>UK: Foreign banks warn UK govt on EMU position - paper.</title>
<headline>Foreign banks warn UK govt on EMU position - paper.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-08-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Foreign banks in London have told the government that the role of London's City as a financial centre is being damaged by Britain's right to opt out of European monetary union, the Financial Times reported.</p>
<p>The Foreign Banks and Securities Houses Association, in a letter to the UK treasury, has called for Britain to make a decision on particpating in monetary union, arguing that the uncertainty harms their members' ability to plan, the newspaper said.</p>
<p>The association represents 180 financial institutions in London.</p>
